0. Prepare release (im master for .0 release or in release/2.12 else)
* String Freeze (14 days before recommended)
* Update splash screen src/frontend/splash.png
* Update the statistics in admin/SLOC.txt, admin/README.git-stats and in data/examples/SLOC History.lml
* in master (+ cherry-pick to release/2.12)
	* add release with date in org.kde.labplot.appdata.xml
	* Set release date in Changelog
* (master|release/2.12) CMakeLists.txt: project(labplot VERSION 2.12.0 LANGUAGES CXX C)
* Make sure no case-sensitive conflicting files exits

------------------------------------------------------------

1. Tag the release (in master for .0, release/2.12 else. TODO: Use tagme from releaseme? see https://community.kde.org/ReleasingSoftware)
* Commit everything and "git push labplot"
* git tag "2.12.0" -a -m "2.12.0 Release"
* git push --tags (invent.kde.org: create new Access Token [API access] and use this one)


2. [Release day] Create source tarball (see https://invent.kde.org/sdk/releaseme, @openSUSE 16.0/Tumbleweed):
* Install releaseme: git clone https://invent.kde.org/sdk/releaseme
* Wait for pipelines (of tag) to finish
* Create the tarball, from the releaseme folder execute tarme.rb like this (needs gpg passphrase):
./tarme.rb --version 2.12.0 --origin trunk labplot

origin can be trunk (== master, .0) or stable (== release/2.12) (see [1], else).
tarme.rb will also calculate the checksums and give a link to create a sysadmin ticket.


3. Create new stable branch:	(Only for .0 release. TODO: Use branchme from releaseme?)
git checkout -b release/2.12
git push kde:labplot release/2.12
git remote update
git branch --set-upstream-to=origin/release/2.12
* Update [1]
* Update [2]
* Update fork of sysadmin/ci-utils on invent.kde.org ad update
	[3] & [4] via a single MR of fork
* Enable CD in .gitlab-ci.yml of release/2.12 (appimage, windows, macos_x86+amd64 "master"->"release/2.12")


4. Create Installer (.0: when macOS MR is done)
* Rebuild packages (AppImage, Win, macos-arm64+x86_64) on CD (release/2.12 branch)
* Test preliminary packages


5. Upload tarball labplot-2.12.0.tar.xz and signature labplot-2.12.0.tar.xz.sig to ftp://upload.kde.org/incoming (Read readme: ftp://upload.kde.org/README)
	kdecp labplot-2.12.0.tar.xz ftp://upload.kde.org/incoming
	kdecp labplot-2.12.0.tar.xz.sig ftp://upload.kde.org/incoming
	[or filezilla]


6. Sysadmin ticket
* File a syadmin ticket to register new project versions on Bugzilla and move the files to the stable/labplot folder
* Use the template for the ticket (generated by releaseme; flat target, checksum included):

